est, need sum 22 or 33 or 11 from y+m+d.\n- 1986-08-08 → 1986+8+8 = 2002 → 2+0+0+2 = 4. Not master.\n- 1986-11-11 → 1986+11+11 = 2008 → 2+0+0+8 = 10 → 1. Not master.\n- 1990-09-09 → 1990+9+9 = 2008 → 4\n- 1970-04-29 → 1970+4+29 = 2003 → 5\n- 1959-12-29 → 1959+12+29 = 2000 → 2\n- 1+9+8+6+0+8+0+8 = 40 → 4. \n\nThe stub reduces by summing digits until <=9 OR equals 11/22/33. So if intermediate sum hits 11/22/33 it keeps it. The \"ano_pessoal\" formula in stubPilar1Cabala: `anoBase + aniversario.getMonth() + aniversario.getDate()`. If mes=11, dia=29, base=2026, sum = 2026+10+29 = 2065 → 2+0+6+5=13 → 1+3=4. So master numbers in ano_pessoal are hard.\n\nFor life_path, I need y+m+d to reduce to 11/22/33.\n- 2000-01-01 → 2002 → 4\n- 1987-11-15 → 1987+11+15=2013 → 2+0+1+3=6\n- For 11: y+m+d=11, 29, 38, 47, 56, 65, 74, 83, 92, 101, 110, 119, 128, 137, 146, 155, 164, 173, 182, 191, 209, 218, 227, 236, 245, 254, 263, 272, 281, 290, 308, ... \n- Actually any sum 29 reduces: 2+9=11, so 11 is kept (master). So y+m+d=29, 38, 47, 56, 65, 74, 83, 92, 101, 110, 119, ... etc. Also sum=38 reduces to 11. Sum=47 → 11. Sum=56 → 11. Sum=92 → 11. Sum=101 → 2. So 29, 38, 47, 56, 65, 74, 83, 92 yield 11. 92 = 1957+1+34 = 1992... no 1957+1+34=1992. 1992-01-01+34 = 34, so 1965+12+20 = 1997... Let me try 1987-08-24 → 1987+8+24=2019 → 2+0+1+9=12 → 1+2=3. No. Try 1971-01-08 → 1971+1+8=1980 → 1+9+8+0=18 → 1+8=9.\n\nEasier: 2002-08-26 → 2002+8+26 = 2036 → 2+0+3+6=11 ✅. \n\nFor 22: y+m+d=22, 40, 49, 58, 67, 76, 85, 94, 103, 112, 121, 130, 139, 148, 157, 166, 175, 184, 193, 202, 211, 220...\n- 2002-11-27 → 2002+11+27=2040 → 2+0+4+0=6. No wait, 22 is master but 40 → 4+0=4, not 22. Need to check: the stub reduces \"until n>9 and n != 11/22/33\". So if intermediate is 22, it stays. Let me trace: y+m+d=40. Sum digits: 4+0=4. So 40→4, not 22. Hmm.\n- For 22 we need y+m+d to BE 22 (or 11 stays 11 → not 22). So y+m+d=22, 49 (4+9=13→1+3=4, not 22), 58 (5+8=13→4), 67 (13→4), 76 (13→4), 85 (13→4), 94 (13→4), 103 (4), 112 (4), 121 (4), 130 (4), 139 (4), 148 (4), 157 (4), 166 (4), 175 (4), 184 (4), 193 (4), 202 (4), 211 (4), 220 (4+0=4 not 22)... Actually sum must literally equal 22 or 11 or 33 at some step.\n- y+m+d=22: 1980-01-01 → 1980+1+1=1982 → 1+9+8+2=20 → 2. No. Try 1960-01-01 → 1962 → 1+9+6+2=18 → 9. No. Try 1990-11-01 → 1990+11+1=2002 → 4. No. Try 1975-04-25 → 1975+4+25=2004 → 6. Try 2002-08-12 → 2002+8+12=2022 → 2+0+2+2=6. \n- What about y+m+d=22 with year like 2011-01-10 → 2022 → 6. Or 2000-10-12 → 2000+10+12=2022 → 6. \n- Try 1979-01-02 → 1982 → 20 → 2.\n- 1990-12-01 → 2003 → 5.\n- 1995-05-22 → 2022 → 6.\n- 1996-01-25 → 2022 → 6.\n- 1999-01-22 → 2022 → 6.\n- 2000-11-11 → 2022 → 6.\n- 1986-08-12 → 2006 → 8. \n- 2002-01-19 → 2022 → 6.\n- 2003-12-07 → 2022 → 6.\n- 2001-01-20 → 2022 → 6.\n- 1988-10-24 → 2022 → 6.\n\nHmm, getting 22 is hard. Let me see: y+m+d=22 directly:\n- 2010-11-01 → 2022 → 6. Wait y=2010, m=11, d=1, sum=2022.\n- Try: 1990-10-22 → 2022 → 6\n- 1979-04-29 → 2012 → 5\n- I see the issue. y is always 19xx or 20xx, so y alone is 4 digits. y+m+d will be at minimum ~1900+1+1=1902.\n\nLet me just verify: 2002-08-12 → y+m+d=2002+8+12=2022 → 2+0+2+2=6. So 22 is NEVER reachable from 4-digit y. The maximum 2-digit intermediate would be from ~1+9+8+0=18 or 1+9+6+2=18 etc. So life_path can be 1-9, 11 only if intermediate is 11, 22/33 impossible.\n\nMaster 11: y+m+d must reduce to 11. y=1xxx, so y digit sum is 1+9+9+x for 1990s = 1+9+9+y4+y5. For 1990: 1+9+9+0=19. For 1987: 1+9+8+7=25 → 7. For 1984: 1+9+8+4=22 → 4. So 4-digit y already sums to single digit usually. Then sum+m+d: e.g., 1+9+9+0=19, +m+d. For 1990-11-11: 19+11+11=41 → 5. For 1990-01-01: 19+1+1=21 → 3.\n\nOK the stub is more of a placeholder. The test just needs to ensure determinism + 1-9/11 range. Let me not focus on master number validation since the stub is simplified.\n\nSimpler: 10 profiles + 10 tests. Validation = (1) Zod accepts, (2) calcular() returns shape, (3) deterministic, (4) crisis detection works, (5) cita fontes per pilar.\n\nLet me write the fixture + test.","signature":"1aab79dc1c598d6c4bf721d18985d4fa23092a52665a690085c7f91c1abac6ea"}],"model":"MiniMax-M3","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard"},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c0787fb7-82fa-44f6-9d17-dcf4b664ec3c","uuid":"9ee88eea-8b32-4c39-a689-44b3b0f743b0"}
