{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0679c82dc06d0f3031d15fe5e8650c1c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me also check the rest of correlation-map (line 100+) and see the ifaToCabalaMap continuation, then I can write a D-044 validator test.\n\nThe validation should check:\n1. **No invented correspondences**: every key in IFA_ODUS, SEFIRot, ICHING_NAMES exists in canonical sources\n2. **Internal consistency**: same Odu maps to same sefirot from different paths\n3. **Range valid**: I Ching hexagrams 1-64, Sefirot 1-10, Odu 16 names\n4. **No overlaps/contradictions** in maps\n5. **Citations**: all maps cite source (Doc 06 §2 in AGENTS.md or the research files)\n\nLet me also see if there's a `correlation-engine.ts` that uses these maps, and check the existing correlation-map.test.ts (361 lines).\n\nBut actually the user task is to use the **cabala-corr-validator agent** which exists in the Agent tool. Let me check its scope: it was \"Valida correspondências esotéricas propostas para o projeto Cabala dos Caminhos antes de serem adicionadas a IDEIA.md.\"\n\nBut the agent has no Write/Edit access — only Read/Grep/Glob. So it's read-only validation. The TODO D-044 says \"Validar com cabala-corr-validator\" — could be:\n1. Spawn the agent to audit the canonical maps\n2. Write a vitest test that does automated validation\n3. Both\n\nGiven context budget, let me do BOTH: write a vitest test for automated checks (fast, no agent cost), AND summarize findings.\n\nLet me write `packages/akasha-core/src/correlation-validation.test.ts`:\n- Range checks: IFA_ODUS has 16 unique entries; SEFIRot has 10; I Ching 1-64\n- ifaToIchingMap: all values in 1-64, no duplicates across Odus\n- sefirotToTrigramMap: all values in 1-8 (King Wen trigrams)\n- ifaToCabalaMap: all values in 1-10 (Sefirot)\n- Determinism: same input → same output via getIchingsByIfa, getSefirotByIfa, etc\n- Backward coverage: every Odu in IFA_ODUS has a mapping (no orphans)\n- All 16 Odu names in IFA_ODUS appear in IfaOdu union type\n\nThen a short D-044 COT documenting the validation + any gaps.\n\nLet me also quickly check if IFA_ODUS is missing Ogbe (the actual first Odu in Ifá tradition). Looking at line 31: IFA_ODUS starts with 'Oyekun' — but in Ifá tradition, the 16 principal Odus are: Ogbe (or Ogbè), Oyeku, Iwori, Odi, Irosun, Owonrin, Obara, Okanran, Ogunda, Osa, Ika, Oturupon, Otura, Irete, Ofun, Ose. So **Ogbe is missing** and **Ofun is missing** and **Eji (which is Ogbe+Oyeku combined)** is added. The ifaToCabalaMap won't work for Ogbe because it's not in the union. Hmm.\n\nActually the akasha-core stub uses:\n```\nconst odus16 = ['Ogbe', 'Oyeku', 'Iwori', 'Odi', ...];\n```\n\nSo the stub's \"odus16\" includes \"Ogbe\" but correlation-map's IFA_ODUS does NOT include \"Ogbe\". This is **a divergence** between R-030's stub and the correlation-map. That's a finding for D-044.\n\nLet me also check the ifaToCabalaMap to ensure all Sefirot numbers are in 1-10:\n- Oyekun: [1, 10] ✓\n- Iwori: [2, 3] ✓\n- Odi: [4, 5] ✓\n- Irosun: [6, 7] ✓\n- Owonrin: [8, 9, 10] ✓\n- Obara: [10, 6] ✓\n- Okanran: [3, 7] ✓\n- Ogunda: [4, 5] ✓\n- Osa: [1, 10] ✓\n- Ika: [8, 9] ✓\n\nLooks consistent.\n\nBut: where are the citations? Lines 31+ have IFA_ODUS array but no doc reference. The instinto said: \"CORRELATION_MAP (Phase 1) já é a fonte canônica derivada de Doc 06 §2\". Let me search for \"Doc 06\" or \"Doc 6\" or \"06 §2\" references.","signature":"4ce1b881245729014b0275b7ea49e8e6e999a2f5d31b2cb7c14331853b5dc441"}],"model":"MiniMax-M3","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard"},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c0787fb7-82fa-44f6-9d17-dcf4b664ec3c","uuid":"3edfc4d2-374b-494c-b738-0b8b244477e5"}
